Nightowl Photo Editor

This is a simple photo editor application created using Python and Tkinter. 
It allows users to adjust the brightness, contrast, and blur of images, as well as rotate, flip, and add borders to them.

Features:

Adjust brightness, contrast, and blur
Rotate and flip images
Add borders to images
Save edited images
Instructions:

Click the "Select Image" button to open an image file.
Use the sliders to adjust the brightness, contrast, and blur of the image.
Use the combo boxes to rotate, flip, and add borders to the image.
Click the "Save" button to save the edited image to a new file.
Example:

To blur an image:

Open an image file.
Move the "Blur" slider to the desired level.
Click the "Save" button to save the blurred image to a new file.
Requirements:

Python 3.6+
Tkinter
Pillow
Installation:

To install the Nightowl Photo Editor, simply download the code and run the following command:

python main.py
Usage:

To use the Nightowl Photo Editor, simply run the main.py file. 
This will open the application window. You can then select an image file to edit and adjust the settings to your liking. 
Once you are finished editing the image, you can save it to a new file by clicking the "Save" button.
